<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100413258425243></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100413258425243><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6887&mid=100413258425243>RE: Backstabs</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6887&mid=100413258425243#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83851><span id= >Siri</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 26th 5:43 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Didn't everyone already have this discussion when RB was posted?&nbsp;&nbsp;:)<br><br>Unless the old info was wrong, 40% haste increases attacks by 40%.  That is NOT the same as reducing delay by 40% (increasing attacks by 100% = reducing delay by 50%, for example).<br><br>To recap, RB is 15/25, but with 40% haste:<br><br>60 s/min x 1 attack/2.5 s = 24 attacks/min<br>24 attacks/min x 1.4 = 33.6 attacks/min hasted<br>33.6 attacks/min x 1 min/60 s = 1 attack/[A] s<br>[A] = 1.786 s<br>[hasted delay] = 10[A] = 17.86<br><br>This is without double attack, attack buff from Seething Fury, etc., and assuming Delay = 10 x [actual delay in seconds].<br><br>Now, Mrylokar's Dagger of Vengeance (15/19) with 40% haste:<br><br>60 s/min x 1 attack/1.9 s = 31.579 attacks/min<br>31.579 attacks/min x 1.4 = 44.211 attacks/min hasted<br>44.211 attacks/min x 1 min/60 s = 1 attack/[A] s<br>[A] = 1.357 s<br>[hasted delay] = 10[A] = 13.57<br><br>So after 40% haste:<br><br>Ragebringer - 15/17.86<br>Mrylokar's Dagger of Vengeance - 15/13.57<br><br>This is similar to what Fyrewalker posted, only this also gives the accurate damage and delay, not just the ratio between them.<br><br>Now I just need to quit my job and join an uberguild so I can get one.  :)<br><br><br>Siri, Rodcet Nife<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
